         <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" source="#ala2004">
            <p>For the good fortune of the splendid metropolis of the Aphrodisians, this work of the <foreign xml:lang="la">palaestra</foreign> also took place 
               <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">under Flavius Ampelius</supplied> the most eloquent <foreign xml:lang="la">scholasticus</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="la">pater</foreign>, 
               in the tenth indiction. With good fortune.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" source="#jmr2008b">
            <p>For the good fortune of the splendid [metrop]olis of the Aphrodisians, this work of the <foreign xml:lang="la">palaestra</foreign> also took place under
               <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">Flavius Ampelius</supplied> the most eloquent <foreign xml:lang="la">scholasticus</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="la">pater</foreign>, 
               in the 10th indiction. With good fortune.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#CMR">
            <p>For the good fortune of the splendid metropolis of the Aphrodisians, this work of the <foreign xml:lang="la">palaestra</foreign> also took place 
               <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">under Flavius Ampelius</supplied> the most eloquent <foreign xml:lang="la">scholasticus</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="la">pater</foreign>, 
               in the tenth  most fortunate indiction.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            
            <p>For Ampelios, see also <ref type="inscription" n="38" target="iAph040202"/>, <ref type="inscription" n="22" target="iAph120101"/> and <ref type="inscription" n="44" target="iAph080609"/>.</p>
         </div>
